"Isaiah 59:5
They hatch adders’ eggs;
they weave the spider’s web;
he who eats their eggs dies,
and from one that is crushed a viper is hatched." — Isaiah 59:5

"Psalm 92:4
For you, O LORD, have made me glad by your work;
at the works of your hands I sing for joy." — Psalm 92:4

"Psalm 29:2
Ascribe to the LORD the glory due his name;
worship the LORD in the splendor of holiness." — Psalm 29:2

"Psalm 31:5
Into your hand I commit my spirit;
you have redeemed me, O LORD, faithful God." — Psalm 31:5

"Psalm 27:14
Wait for the LORD;
be strong, and let your heart take courage;
wait for the LORD!" — Psalm 27:14

"Psalm 62:8
Trust in him at all times, O people;
pour out your heart before him;
God is a refuge for us. Selah" — Psalm 62:8

"Habakkuk 1:8
Their horses are swifter than leopards,
more fierce than the evening wolves;
their horsemen press proudly on.
Their horsemen come from afar;
they fly like an eagle swift to devour." — Habakkuk 1:8

"Nahum 1:2
God’s Wrath Against Nineveh
The LORD is a jealous and avenging God;
the LORD is avenging and wrathful;
the LORD takes vengeance on his adversaries
and keeps wrath for his enemies." — Nahum 1:2

"Psalm 112:7
He is not afraid of bad news;
his heart is firm, trusting in the LORD." — Psalm 112:7

"Psalm 149:2
Let Israel be glad in his Maker;
let the children of Zion rejoice in their King!" — Psalm 149:2

"Psalm 33:13
The LORD looks down from heaven;
he sees all the children of man;" — Psalm 33:13

"Psalm 66:2
sing the glory of his name;
give to him glorious praise!" — Psalm 66:2

"Psalm 36:9
For with you is the fountain of life;
in your light do we see light." — Psalm 36:9

"Isaiah 40:11
He will tend his flock like a shepherd;
he will gather the lambs in his arms;
he will carry them in his bosom,
and gently lead those that are with young." — Isaiah 40:11

"Psalm 65:11
You crown the year with your bounty;
your wagon tracks overflow with abundance." — Psalm 65:11

"Psalm 36:9
For with you is the fountain of life;
in your light do we see light." — Psalm 36:9

"Isaiah 49:16
Behold, I have engraved you on the palms of my hands;
your walls are continually before me." — Isaiah 49:16

"Isaiah 33:16
he will dwell on the heights;
his place of defense will be the fortresses of rocks;
his bread will be given him; his water will be sure." — Isaiah 33:16

"Isaiah 33:17
Your eyes will behold the king in his beauty;
they will see a land that stretches afar." — Isaiah 33:17

"Psalm 93:2
Your throne is established from of old;
you are from everlasting." — Psalm 93:2

"Lamentations 3:58
“You have taken up my cause, O Lord;
you have redeemed my life." — Lamentations 3:58

