O Jerusalem, herald of good news;
lift it up, fear not;
say to the cities of Judah,
“Behold your God!”" — Isaiah 40:9

"Psalm 74:17
You have fixed all the boundaries of the earth;
you have made summer and winter." — Psalm 74:17

"Song of Solomon 4:7
You are altogether beautiful, my love;
there is no flaw in you." — Song of Songs 4:7

"Song of Solomon 4:7
You are altogether beautiful, my love;
there is no flaw in you." — Song of Songs 4:7

"Psalm 68:10
your flock found a dwelling in it;
in your goodness, O God, you provided for the needy." — Psalm 68:10

"Habakkuk 3:6
He stood and measured the earth;
he looked and shook the nations;
then the eternal mountains were scattered;
the everlasting hills sank low.
His were the everlasting ways." — Habakkuk 3:6

"Psalm 84:7
They go from strength to strength;
each one appears before God in Zion." — Psalm 84:7

"Joel 2:13
and rend your hearts and not your garments.”
Return to the LORD your God,
for he is gracious and merciful,
slow to anger, and abounding in steadfast love;
and he relents over disaster." — Joel 2:13

"Isaiah 41:10
fear not, for I am with you;
be not dismayed, for I am your God;
I will strengthen you, I will help you,
I will uphold you with my righteous right hand." — Isaiah 41:10

"Deuteronomy 32:5
They have dealt corruptly with him;
they are no longer his children because they are blemished;
they are a crooked and twisted generation." — Deuteronomy 32:5

"Psalm 74:16
Yours is the day, yours also the night;
you have established the heavenly lights and the sun." — Psalm 74:16
